	   <tr><td colspan=2>Interesting...<br><br>My group consisted of<br><br>36 cleric<br>38 shadowknight<br>39 bard<br>38 enchanter<br>40 druid<br>40 rogue<br><br>Probably about equal in power to your group. Also happened to be the best pick-up group of my life. However, when we had to break the room, the queen was up.<br><br>We scouted the room, it had 2 webmasters, queen, 2 spiders, and 2 velium crawlers in the water. Basically we went in and got our ass kicked. We DID take the queen down, but the main looter had a robe and they were lore, so the robe rotted. Druid said "evac?" And preceeded to evac, but I had divine aura up and so got left behind :P. I died... the group ran back... got my corpse and looted.<br><br>Round 2. Queen's first body decayed, then queen popped AGAIN. This time we pulled the crawlers through the water to the bridge directly before her room, leaving Miss Thang, a crawler, and 2 webmasters for us to deal with. We went in, and even without harmtouch (SK had used it on queen) took her down EASILY. The key was keeping the mobs off the enchanter, and with 3 mobs mezzed we beat down the queen easily.<br><br>After that it was not too much of a problem holding the room. In 4 hrs 30 minutes of camping, our group got 4 bubbles of experience each and the following loot:<br><br>1 Crystalline sword<br>5 Crystal webshields<br>2 Crystalline robes (one rotted)<br>3 Crystal grinders<br>2 Messengers of the queen (Paladin only piercer)<br><br>Even though I died once, I won the roll on a sword, a robe, a grinder, and a piercer, so it was a very, very good night for us.<br><br>By the way, Queenie popped 4 times, Dracnid Retainer popped 6 times, Grinder popped 3 times. The retainer can spawn either as a PH for the queen OR outside in the hallway. A webmaster can also be a PH for queen. Grinder spawns randomly in the long tunnels between stalags and queen room.<br><br>Overall this dungeon is awesome. Beats the tar out of Lower Guk's 30 crap respawn, train-prone, terrible pathing, dungeon from hell. By the way, the Crystalline Sword is much better than a ykesha.<br><br>Good luck adventurers, and have fun in the Crystal Caverns!<br><br>Regards,<br>Mendin Woonds<br>36 Cleric of Tunare<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
